		<!-- message -->
		<div id="post_message_1231635">
                  
                  The fundamentally flawed placement of the GYs in WSG is an obvious problem, especially with those people who think GY camping is a honorable sport. (If I had the powers, I'd take 1 honor per 1 dmg from each foreign player in l.o.s. + range of a foreign GY in WSG...) I'd move the GY outwards (i.e. north for alliance, south for horde) and slightly uphill (i.e. only reachable by having to walk a 3/4-circle-ramp around it, no simple waltzing over the GY straight from the flag room).<br />
<br />
It's IMHO even worse for the AB GYs and the spawn logic. Clearly, when you've got only one base left, you should have a random chance to spawn there or in the home zone. I'd say it should be 80% base, 20% home. If you have more than one, it should always be an almost even chance between all bases, better chance for the closest base (maybe double for closest compared to other chances, i.e. 2:1:1 for 4 bases, 2:1:1 for 3 bases).<br />
IOW: I'd make the respawn logic not just dependent on where a player died. That'd open a lot more 'opportunities'... <img src="images/smilies/wink.gif" border="0" alt="" title="Wink" class="inlineimg" /><br />
<br />
That the home zone in AB desperately needs a second exit, is another obvious problem that should have been fixed long before day one. (Home zone, see above, -1 honor / 1 dmg...) Alternatively (and my favourite) there would be an extra, well-placed spawn point that activates when you have no more bases left.<br />
<br />
Another two things I'd really like to see: (Or maybe it's already done, haven't PVPt in a long time...)<br />
a) Fix the 'moving target' spirit rezzer problem. It annoys me to no end, that the server places me at a GY, but the spirit rezzer is moved at the same time and I have to walk across the map. Maybe only a problem for slower computers, still it should be fixed one way or the other. (Preferably a grace period for the moving?)<br />
b) Let ghosts move a *lot* faster in PVP areas. If I fell to the 'moved spirit rezzer but not you' issue of a) and have to walk, even as a NE, it takes too bloody long. This is PVP, not some sightseeing tour, it's fast paced, so everyone should be back in action 'fast'. Same for the 'only one base left' issue: if it's 4:1 and I try to walk dead from the home zone to the one base, the game is very likely over before I get there.<br />
<br />
After those changes, I'd change the timer considerably: It's plain stupid how fast a 5:0 game is over. I'd only allow it to tick so fast if no battle has been taking place in the last minute, i.e. if one side *really* has given up. (Maybe restrict that to battles 'somewhat close' to a flag, if people whine too hard after the change...)<br />
<br />
I'd scale the timers along 3:2 = 25m, 4:1 = 20m, 5:0 = 15m. (And naturally, the no-honor-for-nth-death thingy is nowadays just a stupid residue of the old honor system that has to go the way of the dodo.)<br />
<br />
About the exploits, I don't know about the current status, but I'd wager that there's still a stupid amount of trivial exploits that should be fixed - one of the reasons I stopped PVP was that I felt ashamed as a Horde to see people in WSG exploit the Horde home-upper-entrance-jump-exploit.<br />
<br />
That's my 2cts (plus change)...<br />
<br />
(As this is rants: All misspellings are intended. Incomplete or insensible sentences are on purpose. What I wrote has nothing to do with what I actually meant. <img src="images/smilies/evil.gif" border="0" alt="" title="Evil" class="inlineimg" /> )
                  
		</div>
		<!-- / message -->
	
		
		
		
