	<td class="alt1" id="td_post_1232016">
	
		
		<!-- message -->
		<div id="post_message_1232016">
                  
                  Not the brightest idea IMHO.<br />
<br />
a) Imagine the start of the battle. Both sides stand in front of the opposite flag pole. Knowing that the one who picks first, loses, both wait for the other side to pick up.<br />
That's even MORE boring than the current situation.<br />
(Even worse, both pickup, both drop again, pickup again, drop again... that'll be an exhilarating experience!)<br />
<br />
b) There's always some &quot;person with a weird sense of humor&quot;, who will pick up the flag, and not return it despite the perfect circumstances. The suggestion does help against this scenario somewhat, but goes overboard in the AE logic. There's no reason to punish other players for one player's stupidity.<br />
<br />
I'd rather prefer somewhat like this:<br />
1. *Voluntarily* dropping the flag gives a **30** second debuff to the previous holder that makes it impossible to pick it up again.<br />
2. The flag automatically drops every 90 seconds once, giving a 15 second debuff to the previous holder.<br />
3. The flag only returns after a period of 10 seconds when nobody (tried to) pick it up. I.e. the debuff allows trying which allows the flag to *stay* for retaking it after the debuff fades.<br />
4. (Slightly unrelated: ) The flags get multiple spawn points in the bases.<br />
<br />
#include &lt;rants/disclaimer.h&gt;
                  
		</div>
		<!-- / message -->
	
		
		
		
		
		
	
	</td>
