	<td class="alt1" id="td_post_1232699">
	
		
		<!-- message -->
		<div id="post_message_1232699">
                  
                  I really dont think they need to make too many changes to the game.<br />
It's still my favorite battle ground.<br />
<br />
Of course I don't PvP for gear, so 2 hours matches don't frustrate me, they usually are something I enjoy.  Most 2 hour matches require some sort of teamwork to get out of.<br />
<br />
Of course, I also enjoy FPS games, so the idea of playing in a match like that is the reward of PvP.  It's better than playing on a PvP+ Server, where option1 in any attack is to run away no matter what.  Large scale battles with secondary objectives are kinda my thing when it comes to PvP, I personally think Blizzard has gotten a lot more right than wrong in their battlegrounds.<br />
<br />
The only thing I think they screwed the pooch on was Arena gear.  It's miles away better than any other old Honor gear for pvp, and it's designed specifically for pvp, with high sta and resiliance on every piece.  You are almost forced to get it to compete.  Instead of it being alternate advancement, it's required advancement.  That wouldn't be so bad except, without this gear, it takes 2+ months to get the points to get the gear in the first place.  Forcing people to lose for 2-3 months before they get to compete in a PvP battleground on equal footing is just plain dumb.<br />
<br />
Maybe when they move season 1 arena to the honor brokers it'll even things out a little more and be a bit better, for now tho I don't bother with pvp on any of my 70s, instead I pvp on my various lowbies, 19-49 (some parked, without being twinked, at certain ranges).<br />
<br />
-Att.
                  
		</div>
		<!-- / message -->
	
		
		
		
		
		
	
	</td>
</tr>
